<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Natal Chart Analysis Tool — A Grounded Method</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400;1,500&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        :root {
            --navy:        #2c3e50;
            --accent:      #8b3a2a;
            --accent-soft: #c17a5e;
            --accent-faint:#f0e8e4;
            --gold:        #b8860b;
            --gold-faint:  #faf4e1;
            --paper:       #f7f5f0;
            --paper-dark:  #ede9e1;
            --ink:         #1a1a1a;
            --ink-muted:   #5a5a5a;
            --ink-faint:   #9a9a9a;
            --border:      rgba(26,26,26,0.12);
            --white:       #ffffff;
            --green:       #27ae60;
        }

        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

        body {
            font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
            background: var(--paper);
            color: var(--ink);
            line-height: 1.7;
        }

        /* ── MASTHEAD ── */
        .masthead {
            background: var(--navy);
            color: white;
            padding: 5rem 2rem 4rem;
            text-align: center;
            position: relative;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .masthead::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            inset: 0;
            background: repeating-linear-gradient(
                45deg, transparent, transparent 40px,
                rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 40px,
                rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 41px
            );
        }

        .masthead::after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
            height: 4px;
            background: var(--accent-soft);
        }

        .masthead-eyebrow {
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            letter-spacing: 0.22em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            position: relative;
        }

        .masthead h1 {
            font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
            font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5.5vw, 3.8rem);
            font-weight: 500;
            line-height: 1.12;
            color: white;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            position: relative;
        }

        .masthead h1 em {
            font-style: italic;
            color: var(--accent-soft);
        }

        .masthead-divider {
            width: 40px;
            height: 2px;
            background: var(--accent-soft);
            margin: 1.5rem auto;
            position: relative;
        }

        .masthead-sub {
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
            max-width: 460px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            font-weight: 300;
            position: relative;
            line-height: 1.75;
        }

        /* ── LAYOUT ── */
        .container {
            max-width: 760px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 3.5rem 2rem 5rem;
        }

        /* ── FRAMING NOTE ── */
        .framing {
            background: white;
            border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
            padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        .framing strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 600; }

        /* ── SECTION HEADER ── */
        .section-header {
            display: flex;
            align-items: baseline;
            gap: 1rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
            padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--ink);
        }

        .section-num {
            font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
            font-size: 3.2rem;
            font-weight: 400;
            color: var(--paper-dark);
            line-height: 1;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .section-title-wrap { flex: 1; }

        .section-eyebrow {
            display: block;
            font-size: 0.68rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            letter-spacing: 0.15em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--ink-faint);
            margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
        }

        .section-title {
            font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: var(--ink);
            line-height: 1.2;
        }

        .section { margin-bottom: 3.5rem; }

        /* ── STEP CARDS ── */
        .steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; }

        .step {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr;
            background: white;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-top: none;
            opacity: 0;
            transform: translateY(12px);
            animation: fadeUp 0.4s ease forwards;
        }

        .step:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
        .step:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0.1s; }
        .step:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }
        .step:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.3s; }
        .step:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }
        .step:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 0.5s; }

        @keyframes fadeUp {
            to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
        }

        .step-num {
            background: var(--navy);
            color: white;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            min-height: 56px;
        }

        .step-body { padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem; }

        .step-title {
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            color: var(--ink);
            margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
        }

        .step-desc {
            font-size: 0.875rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            line-height: 1.65;
        }

        .step-desc a {
            color: var(--accent);
            font-weight: 600;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent-soft);
            transition: border-color 0.2s;
            -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
        }

        .step-desc a:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }

        /* ── URL CALLOUT ── */
        .url-callout {
            background: var(--gold-faint);
            border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
            padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem;
            margin-top: 0.75rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-between;
            gap: 1rem;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }

        .url-callout-link {
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: var(--navy);
            text-decoration: none;
            letter-spacing: 0.01em;
        }

        .url-callout-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

        .url-callout-note {
            font-size: 0.78rem;
            color: var(--ink-faint);
        }

        /* ── PROMPT BLOCKS ── */
        .prompt-section {
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        .prompt-label {
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            letter-spacing: 0.14em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--ink-faint);
            margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
        }

        .prompt-block {
            background: #1a1a1a;
            border-radius: 3px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .prompt-block-head {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-between;
            padding: 0.7rem 1.1rem;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
            gap: 1rem;
        }

        .prompt-block-meta {
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            color: rgba(255,255,255,0.38);
            font-weight: 500;
            letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        .prompt-block-tag {
            font-size: 0.65rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            background: var(--accent);
            color: white;
            padding: 0.2rem 0.55rem;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .prompt-block-body {
            padding: 1.25rem 1.4rem;
            font-family: 'DM Sans', monospace;
            font-size: 0.82rem;
            line-height: 1.78;
            color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            word-break: break-word;
            overflow-wrap: break-word;
            -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
        }

        .prompt-block-body strong {
            color: var(--accent-soft);
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        /* ── COPY BUTTON ── */
        .copy-btn {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            background: var(--navy);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 0.6rem 1.1rem;
            font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            cursor: pointer;
            margin-top: 0.5rem;
            transition: background 0.2s;
            letter-spacing: 0.03em;
            -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
            touch-action: manipulation;
        }

        .copy-btn:hover { background: var(--accent); }
        .copy-btn.copied { background: var(--green); }

        .copy-icon { font-size: 0.85rem; }

        /* ── NOTES BOX ── */
        .notes-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 0.75rem;
        }

        .note-card {
            background: white;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
            display: flex;
            gap: 0.75rem;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }

        .note-icon {
            font-size: 1rem;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            margin-top: 0.1rem;
        }

        .note-text {
            font-size: 0.875rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            line-height: 1.65;
        }

        .note-text strong {
            display: block;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--ink);
            margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
            font-size: 0.88rem;
        }

        /* ── CLOSING ── */
        .closing {
            margin-top: 3rem;
            background: var(--gold-faint);
            border-top: 3px solid var(--gold);
            padding: 2rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .closing p {
            font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            font-style: italic;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        .closing p strong {
            color: var(--ink);
            font-style: normal;
        }

        /* ── FOOTER ── */
        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--ink-faint);
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        /* ── PROSE ── */
        .prose {
            font-size: 0.92rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            line-height: 1.8;
            margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
        }

        .label-caps {
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            letter-spacing: 0.14em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--ink-faint);
            margin: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;
        }

        /* ── JUNGIAN BADGE ── */
        .optional-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            background: var(--accent-faint);
            color: var(--accent);
            font-size: 0.68rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            letter-spacing: 0.08em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem;
            margin-left: 0.6rem;
            vertical-align: middle;
        }

        /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
        @media (max-width: 600px) {

            /* Masthead */
            .masthead {
                padding: 3rem 1.25rem 2.5rem;
            }
            .masthead-eyebrow {
                font-size: 0.62rem;
                letter-spacing: 0.14em;
            }
            .masthead-sub {
                font-size: 0.88rem;
            }

            /* Layout */
            .container {
                padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem;
            }
            .section {
                margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
            }

            /* Section headers — shrink the large number */
            .section-header {
                gap: 0.6rem;
                margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
            }
            .section-num {
                font-size: 2rem;
            }
            .section-title {
                font-size: 1.3rem;
            }
            .section-eyebrow {
                font-size: 0.62rem;
            }

            /* Framing note */
            .framing {
                padding: 1rem 1rem;
                font-size: 0.875rem;
                margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
            }

            /* Step cards — larger tap targets */
            .step {
                grid-template-columns: 36px 1fr;
            }
            .step-num {
                min-height: 48px;
                font-size: 0.85rem;
            }
            .step-body {
                padding: 0.85rem 0.9rem;
            }
            .step-title {
                font-size: 0.9rem;
            }
            .step-desc {
                font-size: 0.84rem;
            }

            /* URL callout */
            .url-callout {
                flex-direction: column;
                gap: 0.25rem;
                padding: 0.75rem 0.9rem;
            }
            .url-callout-link {
                font-size: 0.82rem;
                word-break: break-all;
            }

            /* Prompt blocks — scrollable on small screens */
            .prompt-block-head {
                flex-direction: column;
                align-items: flex-start;
                gap: 0.4rem;
                padding: 0.65rem 0.9rem;
            }
            .prompt-block-meta {
                font-size: 0.65rem;
            }
            .prompt-block-body {
                padding: 1rem 0.9rem;
                font-size: 0.8rem;
                line-height: 1.7;
                overflow-x: auto;
                -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
                white-space: pre-wrap;
                word-break: break-word;
            }

            /* Copy buttons — full width on mobile */
            .copy-btn {
                width: 100%;
                justify-content: center;
                padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
                font-size: 0.85rem;
                margin-top: 0.4rem;
            }

            /* Notes grid */
            .notes-grid {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
                gap: 0.5rem;
            }
            .note-card {
                padding: 0.85rem 0.9rem;
            }
            .note-text {
                font-size: 0.84rem;
            }

            /* Closing */
            .closing {
                padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
            }
            .closing p {
                font-size: 1rem;
            }

            /* Optional badge wraps on mobile */
            .optional-badge {
                display: block;
                margin-left: 0;
                margin-top: 0.3rem;
                width: fit-content;
            }

            /* Footer */
            footer {
                padding: 1.25rem 1rem;
                font-size: 0.72rem;
            }

            /* Prose */
            .prose {
                font-size: 0.875rem;
            }
            .label-caps {
                font-size: 0.65rem;
            }
        }

        /* Mid-range tablets */
        @media (min-width: 601px) and (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 4rem;
            }
            .masthead {
                padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem 3rem;
            }
            .prompt-block-body {
                font-size: 0.81rem;
            }
            .copy-btn {
                width: 100%;
                justify-content: center;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header class="masthead">
    <div class="masthead-eyebrow">Astrology · Jungian Psychology · Self-Reflection</div>
    <h1>Natal Chart Analysis<br><em>A Grounded Method</em></h1>
    <div class="masthead-divider"></div>
    <p class="masthead-sub">Treat astrology as a symbolic vocabulary for personality patterns — not fate, not prediction. A mirror, not a map.</p>
</header>

<div class="container">

    <div class="framing">
        <strong>What this is.</strong> This tool uses natal chart symbology as a structured starting point for personality pattern analysis, then layers Jungian archetypes to explain the psychological mechanisms behind those patterns. The output is a practical profile — not a horoscope. Be honest rather than flattering. If something doesn't track, say so.
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 0: GET YOUR CHART -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-num">0</div>
            <div class="section-title-wrap">
                <span class="section-eyebrow">Before you begin</span>
                <div class="section-title">Get Your Natal Chart</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="prose">You need a natal chart report before you can run the analysis. CafeAstrology provides a free, detailed report — no account required. You'll need your <strong>date, exact time, and place of birth</strong>.</p>

        <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <div class="step-body">
                    <div class="step-title">Go to the chart calculator</div>
                    <div class="step-desc">Visit <a href="https://astro.cafeastrology.com/natal.php" target="_blank">astro.cafeastrology.com/natal.php</a> and enter your birth date, exact time, and place of birth. Birth time accuracy matters — even a 15-minute difference can shift the Ascendant sign, which shapes the whole analysis.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <div class="step-body">
                    <div class="step-title">Save the full report as PDF</div>
                    <div class="step-desc">Once the report loads, use your browser's Print function (Cmd+P on Mac, Ctrl+P on Windows) and choose <strong>Save as PDF</strong>. Save the entire page — it includes the chart wheel, planet positions, house cusps, aspects table, and written interpretations. All of this is useful source material for the analysis.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <div class="step-body">
                    <div class="step-title">Open your AI assistant</div>
                    <div class="step-desc">Go to <strong>Claude</strong> (claude.ai) or <strong>ChatGPT</strong> (chat.openai.com). Both can read PDF attachments. Start a new conversation and attach the saved PDF before sending Prompt 1 below.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="url-callout">
            <a href="https://astro.cafeastrology.com/natal.php" target="_blank" class="url-callout-link">astro.cafeastrology.com/natal.php</a>
            <span class="url-callout-note">Free · No account required · Saves as PDF</span>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROMPT 1 -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-num">1</div>
            <div class="section-title-wrap">
                <span class="section-eyebrow">First Prompt</span>
                <div class="section-title">Natal Chart Interpretation</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="prose">Attach your PDF and send this prompt. The framing is critical — it tells the model to treat astrology as pattern-matching rather than prediction, and to flag where the analysis is accurate, overstated, or noise.</p>

        <div class="prompt-section">
            <div class="prompt-block">
                <div class="prompt-block-head">
                    <div class="prompt-block-meta">Send to Claude or ChatGPT · with natal chart PDF attached</div>
                    <div class="prompt-block-tag">Astrology as Symbolic Model</div>
                </div>
                <div class="prompt-block-body" id="prompt1-text">I have my natal chart and a written interpretation.

I'd like you to analyse it as a <strong>symbolic personality model</strong>, not as fate, prediction, or belief system.

Please:

<strong>1.</strong> Extract the core themes and tensions the chart points to — in plain language, minimal astrology jargon.

<strong>2.</strong> Translate the chart into psychological and behavioural patterns — how I think, work, relate, handle pressure, autonomy, ambition, and meaning.

<strong>3.</strong> Highlight where astrology is likely accurate, where it's overstated, and where it's probably misleading or symbolic only.

<strong>4.</strong> Reframe the insights into a non-woo, practical profile I can actually reflect on.

Treat this as pattern-matching and narrative analysis, not cosmic truth. Be honest rather than flattering. If something doesn't track, say so.

I'm interested in <strong>insight, not certainty</strong>.</div>
            </div>
            <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyText('prompt1-raw', this)">
                <span class="copy-icon">⎘</span> Copy Prompt 1
            </button>
        </div>

        <div class="label-caps">What to expect</div>
        <p class="prose" style="margin-bottom:0;">The model will return a structured profile covering core tensions (e.g. expression vs. precision), behavioural patterns (how you think, work, handle pressure), an accuracy check flagging what's real signal vs. noise, and a practical summary. This is the foundation layer — mechanism comes next.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- PROMPT 2 -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-num">2</div>
            <div class="section-title-wrap">
                <span class="section-eyebrow">Follow-up Prompt <span class="optional-badge">Optional but recommended</span></span>
                <div class="section-title">Jungian Archetypal Layer</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="prose">Send this in the <strong>same conversation</strong>, immediately after Prompt 1. No need to re-attach the PDF — the model still has it in context. This layer adds the psychological mechanism: not just what the patterns are, but why they exist and where to interrupt them.</p>

        <div class="prompt-section">
            <div class="prompt-block">
                <div class="prompt-block-head">
                    <div class="prompt-block-meta">Send in the same session · no re-attachment needed</div>
                    <div class="prompt-block-tag">Psychological Mechanism Layer</div>
                </div>
                <div class="prompt-block-body" id="prompt2-text">Now run a <strong>Jungian archetypal interpretation</strong> of the same chart.

Use Jung's model not as mysticism but as a psychological mechanism layer:

— The archetypes: Ego, Shadow, Persona, Anima/Animus
— The four functions: Thinking, Feeling, Sensation, Intuition
— The individuation arc as a developmental framework

The goal is to understand <strong>why</strong> the behavioural patterns exist — the mechanism behind them — not just describe what they are.

In particular:
— What does the Shadow reveal about the rescue or over-functioning patterns?
— What is the Inferior Function, and how does it fail under stress?
— What does the individuation arc look like for this chart — where is the transition point?

Be honest about where the Jungian framework earns its place and where it reaches beyond the evidence.</div>
            </div>
            <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyText('prompt2-raw', this)">
                <span class="copy-icon">⎘</span> Copy Prompt 2
            </button>
        </div>

        <div class="label-caps">Why this matters</div>
        <p class="prose" style="margin-bottom:0;">Prompt 1 tells you <em>what</em> the patterns are. Prompt 2 tells you <em>why</em> they exist and where to intervene. The Shadow analysis in particular tends to be the most actionable output — it reframes habitual behaviours as psychological mechanisms rather than personality traits, which changes how you work on them.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- PROMPT 3: SYNTHESIS -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-num">3</div>
            <div class="section-title-wrap">
                <span class="section-eyebrow">Optional Third Step</span>
                <div class="section-title">Operating Model Synthesis</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="prose">Once you have both analyses, ask the model to synthesise them into a usable operating model — the kind of thing you can actually interrupt in real time, not just reflect on afterwards.</p>

        <div class="prompt-section">
            <div class="prompt-block">
                <div class="prompt-block-head">
                    <div class="prompt-block-meta">Send after both prompts · same session</div>
                    <div class="prompt-block-tag">Synthesis</div>
                </div>
                <div class="prompt-block-body" id="prompt3-text">Now synthesise both analyses into a practical operating model.

Specifically:

